text: Yanakie Isthmus is a sandy isthmus that connects Wilsons Promontory to mainland Victoria, south-eastern Australia. The small holiday town of Sandy Point and nearby Shallow Inlet lie on the western side of the isthmus. Yanakie is a Koori name from the Gunai language interpreted as meaning "between waters". ==References== *Yanakie Isthmus at the Gazetteer of Australia Online Category:Isthmuses Category:Wilsons Promontory Category:Coastline of Victoria (Australia)
